  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he would go to his daughter's, because we were-- we had-- we lived in the building.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Two of my aunts-- other aunts lived in the building, and his son.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unlike other holidays which were, like Rosh Hashanah, Yom Kippur, that was-- where we spent a lot of-- a long time in the temple listening to the-- to the cousin and the rabbi speaking and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] waiting for any-- for the [NON-ENGLISH] to [INAUDIBLE] so that we-- the services would be over.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had a temple that was-- the men were sitting on the first floor, and the women were sitting on the second floor.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was like a round-- round dome with balconies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] on Yom Kippur, many people would faint and-- because of the fasting.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a very-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] everyone was at awe, to, and-- and especially on Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was like [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] a-- I don't know how to describe it, but it was like [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] a special atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Like in Hebrew they would say like [HEBREW], [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] a solemn occasion.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then we also had very festive and less religious holidays, like Purim, and-- which we used to get-- we used to go and make noises in the temple with the [INAUDIBLE] and we-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was too small, but my brothers and my father used to get the [NON-ENGLISH], dancing with the Torah.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and-- and Hanukkah was probably the most enjoyable because we had candles, lit candles every night, and-- and drank.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
